title: The God of High School
author: Yongje Park
comment_body: You guys do know the death note they're talking about is from way before the manga was ever created, right? The death note mentioned is the ledger with everyone who has lived or will ever live recorded and their time of death. Jaecheondaesong (Son Goku, Monkey King Enma) was a notorious trouble maker and made himself a god/immortal by erasing the date of his death from it. Son Goku from Dragon Ball is based off the original Monkey King, Son Goku - which is why he had a tail.

comment_body: Fun fact : Imoogi is a popular mythical beast in Korean folklore (sometimes seen in China and Japan too, but I think they are most popular in Korea.) title: The God of High School
author: Yongje Park
comment_body: Believe it or not, he's actually getting stronger from fighting these low level enemies and controlling his strength.  By increasing his level of precision and control, he can better control his energy in fights with enemies who are on the same level.  An example in a video game is a skill that levels up the more you use it.  He is currently leveling up one that he hasn't used very much in the past, but can be extremely valuable at higher levels.

title: The God of High School
author: Yongje Park
comment_body: Oh wow, an interesting twist on Journey to the West. For those who don't know the story, Tathagata sent the monk Xuanzhang (Sun Wukong's master) on a pilgrimage and gives him 3 disciples who are atoning for their sins by protecting him on the journey filled with 81 trials and ordeals. Wukong the head disciple, the pig is second, the guy who got eaten by Tathagata was the third.

comment_body: Honestly, I just reread it, and I realized something. Daewi is now going full force, and that is because all of his pent up stress and frustration. He has been working 17 years trying to get back that girl he loves, and the moment she gets closer she loses it again. He's frustrated that he can't get hee back, and it doesnt help that he just watched Xiaochen die. Daewi has bottled up all of his negative emotions and is finally letting it all out. I mean... his hair is becoming like Dante's. sigh.

title: The God of High School
author: Yongje Park
comment_body: Although it's been mentioned before, the duality between Mori and Mubong is great and they serve as excellent foils. Both started their war against Gods out of revenge but circumstances lead them down different paths. Mori lived as a human and has grown past his desire for revenge and combat. Mubong however tried so desperately to help raise humanity to a level higher than the Gods, that he ended up losing his humanity. Like Dante and Vergil from DevilMayCry, their roles could've been reversed.

Honestly, it hits a bit too close to home, what with Mira trying desperately to make up for her failures, real and perceived, and hating herself for even trying to make things right or earn redemption.  I'm glad those kids were able to forgive her, and that she was able to accept that forgiveness.  I hope she is able to apologise to Daewi and finally end this torture.

comment_body: Man this was a crazy chapter! Sorry for not posting for the past 2 weeks. My anxiety got the better of me and I almost completely lost myself in it. Since my last update I lost 2 more lbs (241/215). I'm going to keep this going because I find that writing about it here will help me keep moving forward. I'll copy this update on the last 2 weeks and post a quote on each that helped me get out of my own funk. Mental health is real, make sure you talk w/someone and let them know what's going on, ty!

comment_body: It's actually fairly in-character for Subhudi to side against Sun Wukong, given that in JttW, he asked Wukong to never mention him as the latter's master because he instantly regretted teaching him.  As for the rest, I love how a combination of Bishop Byron and R's cells allowed for Tam to be used to save the world, and that Ilpyo bet on it all along.  I miss that sly foxy bastard.  And then, the book instantly decided Daewi was good enough.  Hilarious.

comment_body: These last few chapters has been a roller coaster of emotions but I dont know how im gonna survive not reading GOH every friday like i have been for the past 8 years. Thank you for the experience.

comment_body: Before you assume things, please keep in mind that the translations are inaccurate for the later part of this chapter. In the raws, the wording was a little bit off but it was pretty obvious that it was a sibling moment, with Mori just saying that Ahan's the most important person in his life. It's the translations that took things out of proportion like this, and some sentences weren't in the raws at all.

comment_body: And with this, the story has finally concluded. I have a lot of things I want to say honestly, so I‚Äôll start with this. Thank you Yongje Park, thank you for such a wonderful and fulfilling story I was able to read while it was ongoing, I got into your story years ago back in 2016-2017 and it was one of the best things I‚Äôve ever read and continued reading for years. You deserve nothing but praise for the work you put in this story. Below this comment is a thread of all my thoughts of this final.

title: The God of High School
author: Yongje Park
comment_body: Yongje Park I cannot thank you enough for gifting us the absolute masterpiece that is GoH. From  meeting the quirky kid fighting to prove he was unbeatable, to the rage of betrayal watching Moris grandfather get murderer, to the insane hype of having a funeral for Mori Hui and all the other beautiful moments in between the emotions I felt and memories made through this series will last a lifetime. Thank you for a truly unforgettable memory, I truly can't wait to reread it.

title: The God of High School
author: Yongje Park
comment_body: In the history of Webtoon, there once existed a blessed weekly rotation for me. On Monday, Tower of God, tusdays had Noblesse. On Thirsday there was a manhwa called Catharsis and on Friday, Hardcore Leveling warrior, The Gamer and God Of Highschool. Then you'd finish the week with Gosu on Saturday and Sundays. Out of all of these days, my favorite was the Friday because of God of Highschool and for that I thank you author and his team for it is and will probably remain my favorite webtoon ever.
